         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Surveyor Generals ¶ Office Sydney ¶ 19 Jan 80 ¶ Dear Baron ¶  ¶ I send you a specimen of a plant said to have poisoned a number of sheep at Burke. ¶  If without the flowers you can make out what it is...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">80.01.19</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Robert Fitzgerald</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M9, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS found with a specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Phyllanthus</seg> sp. (MEL 1595507). MS annotation by M: 'Answ 20/1/80 FvM'. Letter not found.</p>
               </note>Surveyor Generals</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Office Sydney</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">19 Jan 80</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Baron</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I send you a specimen of a plant said to have poisoned a number of sheep at Burke.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">i.e. Bourke, NSW.</p>
               </note> If without the flowers you can make out what it is I should be obliged for the name and your opinion of it as a poisoner — I also send you a drawing<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Drawing not found; M presumably returned it to Fitzgerald as requested.</p>
               </note> of this plant I found at Hill End which I have no doubt from the places I found it in is a native. <name key="Cheranthera">Cheranthera</name> is not to be found in the Flora<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">'<name key="Cheranthera">Cheranthera</name>' is not in Bentham (1863-78), but there is an entry for <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Cheiranthera</seg>, vol. 1, pp. 127-8.</p>
               </note> so I could not examine as to your conjecture. The anthers were as shown in every flower and could not have been united unless in the hub which I did not examine, thinking I could readily find it in some genus close to <name key="Isotoma">Isotoma</name> Please return this drawing as it is one of the illustration[s] of my private copy of the flora, the genera of which, (where possible) I have been similarly representing</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I remain Dear Baron</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Yours truly</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Robt D Fitzgerald</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Hill End is about sixty miles <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">north west of Bathurst</hi>
               </seg>
               <note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">NSW.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Cheranthera">Cheranthera</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Isotoma">Isotoma</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
